    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The nuanced 2006 sauvignon blanc from Blue Grove Hill, the second label of Capaia, a new producer in Philadelphia, South Africa, is cosmopolitan.</p>
        <p>Its citric tang is found in expert sauvignons for which its winemaker, Manfred Tement, is famed in South Styria, an Austrian region. Its aromatic body evokes rich California sauvignons. Its herbal hints are found in New Zealand sauvignons. It is perfect for oysters.</p>
      </block>
